derivation: from the primitive form of the article (hal);
outline:
1. out there, onwards, further
    1. yonder, beyond (of place)
    2. onwards (of time)
kjv_def: back, beyond, (hence,-) forward, hitherto, thence, forth, yonder.
strongs_def: to the distance, i.e. far away; also (of time) thus far
